values:
Garteth and Andrew in particular should read this and get motivated:

http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/4100284.stm

Casshern and Azumi. 

Very cool Japansese films. Casshern in particular is ace. Superbeing neo-like fight scenes, except good and with samurai swords. And there is actually a point to the film. (war is bad mmmkay). Although if you aren't used to Japanese over acting you might not like it. Go watch some Kabuki. You will understand. 

Actually I have never watched any Kabuki properly. I should. 

Had a BBQ on Saturday. I was the BBQer. I wouldn't like to use the word chef as it is hardly chefing. I made sure nothing burnt too badly. We had about 40 people. It was actually fairly dull for me. But it was good to see a lot of my friends. Got them all out of the way so I don't have to see any of them for six months. 

Although Stu is getting married in 3 weeks so I will see Stu and that little hemisphere of friends then. 

I also bought a laptop this weekend. I plan to do cool things with it. Now I don't have a mini recording set up at home a laptop is useful as I can take it to a rehearsal studio when I need to bang some loud vocals out. Everything else I can do with headphones at home. 

I'm sure I had other things to write about that were probably more important but I should be working. So there.

24 hours after the attacks I am back behind my desk. Not quite business as usual as a lot of people aren't here because they are too scared to come in.

Was admittedly a very scary hour yesterday after it all kicked off, Liverpool St is the closest station to my office - everyone who comes here on the tube gets off there. Amazingly no one was hurt and after a while of ringing round everyone was accounted for, although it took until 15.00 to speak to the last person as most of the mobile networks got jammed very quickly. 

I'm very glad that I opt to walk every day. I get a train to London Bridge and then stroll up here. I don't get to exercise much anymore due to working 45 hours a week and having a 4 month old. I quite enjoy looking at the city too though. If you know your history London is pretty interesting. Anyway ,it is a good job I do walk cos otherwise I could have been on the first train that was blown up. 

It was quite odd ducking under police tape and crossing a crime scene to go home though. That was a new experience. I cross houndsditch every day, there was no police in my line of sight and I was seriously not gonna walk an extra mile around it. 

People here are surprisingly calm and if anything, more friendly than usual. although getting on my train last night was a mission. It was full. As in totally utterly full and more people wanted to get on. It didn't get violent but it could have quite easily as train stewards were pushing people away from the doors. 

Full credit to the authorities though to be fair - almost everything is running today. That is probably helped by large amounts of people staying home but still it is impressive nonetheless. 

Anyway, peace to you all.

I am overdue for an update. I have been keeping a handwritten diary of sorts recently though so the following will be from that but with all the really dull bits left out (so most of it really).

Lena bean is now just over 4 months. She is rolling over and making lots of noise and generally being supercute. She is starting to eat baby food and we are experimenting giving her lots of different stuff to see what she likes. Recently she has started grabbing her spoon and shoving it in her mouth. Clever little monkey.

First half of the month was spent looking for a place to live and trying to secure the flat once we found it.

Finally moved house on the 15th to Kent. That was quite annoying and balls. (belated thanks to Glen here for the offer of Van help but we needed to move on a week day anyways). So many bills it is not even funny.

17th was my first day working  in the telematics industry. Quite interesting. Might not be in two months but it is now. Trains are cunts. Went for lunch in stupidly trendy place with the other members of my team. My first conference of my own will probably be held in San Fran, San Jose or LA. Which is nice. In the next year it looks like I will probably be going to Detroit, Las Vegas, and Berlin again in september.

20-23 June - went to conference in Berlin to observe and help out. Missed Lena and Bel lots. Hotel was nice 5 star job. Went to Brandenberg Gate and ate in revolving restaurant in Berlin TV tower. Berlin is a cool place. Didn't have much time to look around though just a few hours on the monday before we had stuff to do. The tuesday was pretty much a 13 hour day. 16 hour if you include the fact that dinner was mostly spent networking and discussing business. Then Wednesday was 6am to 5pm and then straight to the airport to come back. I didn't even have time to spend my euros. I did a lot of talking and even more listening. Met the head honcho of Gracenote and blagged a free t-shirt, one of their engineers filled me in on some of the stuff they are working on at the minute. The future of car audio looks very cool. Hosted the wednesday afternoon in the main conference hall.

Thurs and Friday were spent in meetings and doing research. There are a lot of acroynms and technical terms in this industry but I am pretty much upto speed now.

Basically the job is going well so far, I'm surrounded by good people who know what they are doing but are also eager to help train me and I'm finding it pretty easy. I'm sure it will get harder though.

I am a bit more settled in our new flat now. I'm sure that will get better over time. It sucks that we pay so much more rent for a place that isn't as nice. But we are next to London so what can you do.

That will do for now. I am tired.

Johnny Vegas. He is fat and gets dirty.

Is it just me or is that not funny? it's just fucking sad.

What makes it worse is that the guy has a pretty sharp wit. He has made me laugh in the past. Particularly when he was on Jonathan Ross.

So why he is pretending to be a fucking retard?

I haven't been this bored by Friday night channel 4 since the word used to be on.
This is the funniest thing in the world.

On first glance this is a very good and exciting idea for cinema goers.

But hang on a minute. Where is the link there?
Cinemas will profit from it and err maybe food retail next to cinemas. Why should lottery money go here? Public good?

Public good my fucking balls. If they wanted to do a public good they could contribute the money to help ease the pension crisis. Actually they could do a 1000 things that would ease pain and suffering instead of giving us more choice of movies to watch.

What fucks me off most here is that if you don't have a brain or if you can't be bothered to think it through this is categorically not a cool and groovy thing, it is a capitalist evil soulfucking thing- half of this money is going to the two biggest chains and they will save the most money as they will drastically reduce their overheads because digital is cheaper. On the other hand it will be very very expensive for arthouse cinemas to convert. Think about how they are deciding which cinemas get converted to digital - in areas that don't currently offer many arthouse films. So areas where only big chains are then. And they are under no obligation to show arthouse movies by the way. They have pledged to.

I wish I could get 11.7 million that would enable me to drastically re-enforce my already dominant marketshare and piss on my smaller competitors AND have the press put a nice  we-do-things-for-the-public-good-cos-we-are-a-cool-and-groovy-corporation-honest spin on it. All in exchange for a pledge.

That would be fucking dandy. Cheers.

But then again who gives a shit really? What am I gonna do? boycott vue? Doubtful as then I would never see anything at the cinema.

Wow! I have so much free choice I must live in a free democratic society.

The internet is just rubbish sometimes. 

It is not the internets fault though it is the people who design websites.

No wonder no one uses public transport in England. All the websites are rubbish. 
It is a mission to look anything up.

I laughed long and hard when Bel and I heard this story on the news yesterday.

I'm not sure how evil a person that makes me. Probably quite evil.

People that stupid should have been removed by natural selection by now though.

Can someone please tell me why the fuck is Ian McKellen on fucking Coronation Street? 

Is the world ending or something? British tv is so shit. I'm amazed we don't all kill ourselves. 

In other news bel and I are looking for a new place to live and a new car to go with my new job.

So far we have narrowed the search down to a few towns in Hertfordshire and Bedfordshire and are hoping to take a Toyota Corolla for a test drive tommorow.

I'm getting sick already describing what my new job is and it has only been two days. So I'm going to post the job description and then refer people to look here.

International Conference Producers are:

'The people within the company who produce our products - Conferences and information. And this is where we make our profits. From conception to implementation the Producer will be driving the event. Conference Producers are expected to research and think up new Conferences. You will be expected to produce the Conference which involves creating a marketable programme, recruiting speakers and negotiating sponsorship. Finally, you will over see the marketing of your own Conference and ensure that it runs smoothly on the day.

The job also involves creating, researching and building major industry web content. However, the ultimate aim of your job will be to help build a global company that operates at the forefront of the "new media" industry - so that means you'll also be expected to play your part in helping to shape and develop the company as a whole.'

I have got the job. 

Smooth. 

Now I must negotiate my contract. Money. Mmmmm. I like money. Money is good.

1. What does your LJ nickname mean?
There once was a guy called Niccolo Machiavelli and he was a politician and philosopher.
He wrote things about why it is good to be a devious fucker. My name is Ven. So I'm warning you all that I'm a devious power hungry little bitch.

2. Elaborate on your icon photo.
It's a picture, get over it.

3. Did you lie about your age anywhere on the net?
Almost always.

4. How many LJ friends do you have?
I dunno. Probably about 5

5. What is your current status?
What kind of status? Who wrote this?
Other people have taken this to mean their mood, my mood today is pensive. 

6. What are you wearing right now?
A plain cream t-shirt and comfy kicking round the house trousers. 

7. What is life to you?
Perception, observation and analysis.

8. What is love to you?
The most important thing.

9. What kind of people do you hate most?
Cowards.

10. What type of people do you like most?
I like so few people I don't think they have sufficient numbers to constitute a 'type'

11. What makes you happy?
Lena, Bel, reading and writing/recording my songs. 

12. Are you musically-inclined?
There is no honest answer to this question that doesn't sound arrogant aside from a simple 'yes'.

13. What would you do if you woke up one morning and found out that the person you love most didn't exist, or was killed?
If they didn't exist I wouldn't miss them would I? If they were killed I would find the killer and torture and maim him/her/them for as long as they were physically able to take it. Then I would piss on their corpses, remove their genitalia and shove it into their mouths. Then I would go looking for their families.

14. If you could go back in time and change ONE thing, what would you do?
I'd go back to the 60s and get my Dad to not work in that asbestos factory so that he would have been around to meet my daughter.  

15. If you MUST be an animal for ONE day, what will you be?
Monkey or cat. Depending on whether I was feeling hyper or chilled on that particular day.

16. Ever had a near-death experience?
Yes. 

17. Name ONE obvious personality quality you have.
Confidence.

18. What's the name of the song that's stuck in your head right now?
babarabartiri by the Quantic Soul Orchestra.

19. Are you happy today?
Erm, yeah I guess.

20. Who will cut and paste this next?
No One.

International Conference Producer second stage interview today.

Not as confident as last week. I'm not good at small talk and being likeable.

Considering that I'm not a hippie, don't particularly like animals and am generally too selfish to care about the environment much, this was quite surprising.

Your brain: 10% interpersonal, 15% visual, 45% verbal, and 30% mathematical!
Congratulations on being 100% smart! The above score breaks down what kind of thinking you most enjoy doing. It says nothing about how good you are at any one, just how interested you are in each, relatively. A substantial difference in scores between two people means, conclusively, that they are different kinds of thinkers.

Matching Summary: Each of us has different tastes. Still, I offer the following advice, which I think is obvious:

  1. Don't date someone if your interpersonal percentages differ by more than 50%.
  2. Don't be friends with someone if your verbal percentages differ by more than 60%.
  3. Don't have sex with someone if their math percentage is over 50%.



My test tracked 4 variables How you compared to other people your age and gender:
You scored higher than 15% on interpersonal
You scored higher than 10% on visual
You scored higher than 96% on verbal
You scored higher than 32% on mathematical
Link: The 4-Variable IQ Test written by chriscoyne on OkCupid Online Dating

Stu came down yesterday and sang Faith In Fiction type things. Did the whole of one song which was quite good going considering. In the same amount of time I would have recorded about 5 sets of vocals but then I have been doing this shit for a while now to be fair.

It was funny seeing him amazed at what I consider a very low tech recording set up.
Though last time I recorded with him was with an 8 track and a drum machine and no overdubs.
Or second takes even. 

vocals are sounding nice so far. His lyrics are really good. I am impatient to finish the whole thing though cos I want to have it to listen to. 

Did radio edits of two All One Surface songs the other day. I felt a bit like a whore but what can you do. Especially as I cut large, large chunks out of one of my favourite songs ever. Oh well. 

Andy and Ele are coming down next weekend. So that is something else to look forward to. Bitches though they are.

I'm also trying to learn how to cook at the minute. My efforts into sauce making have been encouraging so far so I  might move up to something a bit cockier this week. 

Still haven't heard from that cocksmoking job. I might just kill myself if I don't get that. I have an excellent degree and overall I scored 97% on their fucking tests. Their benchmark was 75 for balls sake. Cockmonkeys.

Baby won't stop crying today. She won't listen to reason, it is quite annoying. Poor little thing.

First of all Lena is groovy. Growing and changing a bit every day. Which is nice. Bought her some stuff from the ELC the other day. She can smile now. I know babies aren't meant to be able to smile until they are 6 weeks but she can smile. Maybe not in direct response to external stimulus but she can smile. 

Shaz and the Glenmeister came down for a little visit yesterday. Which was nice. They bought nice things for babylena. Cheers guys. :D Been quite a while since Bel and I have seen them so that was groovy. Watched 'Reefer Madness'. Funny. 

Downloaded leaked NIN tracks and more leaked Fiona Apple tracks this weekend. Fiona stuff is cool. Having a weird reaction to the new NIN songs. I like them and I like listening to them but I'm not impressed by them. Maybe the album as a whole will be more impressive. There is a distinct lack of samples on the songs I've heard so far. There is a bit of weird audio manipulation going on but it is quite subtle. It all just seems a bit simple really. And Dave Grohl's drumming annoys me cos it is so distinctly Dave Grohl drumming. 'Getting Smaller' uses a long build using samples of Trent going 'ahhhhhhh' which is good but, Trent, dude, you've done that exact same thing before. Still looking forward to the album though. 

Had a job interview the other day. Deeds Analysis/Paralegal. Interview went really well. They gave me psychometric tests for about hour and a half. I enjoyed that. Usually tests at interviews are pen and paper things but this was interactive on a pc with a nice set of headphones. I have done less entertaining things for fun on the net. 

hopefully I will get the job cos it will look good on my cv for when I try and get a legal job in the states. 

Plus having money is good.

Looking forward to next weekend. Stu is coming down to record vocals for Faith In Fiction stuff. Been a while (5 years ish) since he has done some singing but I have faith in him. His lyrics are good. If the vocals turn out well that album will kick some serious ass. 

I really do love my own music way too much. 

Speaking of which my new Human V song 'Satan Is Brilliant' has been amusing me all week. It is a cut up of an mp3 sermon I found on the internet. It has amused me so much I might do an Eps worth of songs taking the piss out of religion.

My next target is Brian Welch. He really is asking for it. 

That will do for now.

I have had an intense week.

Moved house on Friday.

Got married on Monday.

My Dad died early Wednesday morning.

Each of these things merits their own posts but as you can imagine it is a little hard to keep on top of everything this week.

Interviewer (henceforth denoted as 'Int') - "so you went to University?"

Me - "Yes. (beat) twice actually."

Int - "Twice?" looking at me as if we were talking about the amount of times I have had syphillis or something.

I nodded.

Int - "so what did you study?"

Me - "Law"

Int - "Law?"

I nodded.

Int - "What made you study law?" (sic)

Me - "It was meant to be hard".

Int - "Excuse me?"

Me - "Law is meant to be one of the more difficult degrees to obtain. I wanted to do something challenging".

Int - "Oh. Was it challenging?"

Me - "No."

Int - "What was the other thing you studied?" (sic)

Me - "Global Ethics"

Int - "And what made you choose that?"

Me - "The course outline interested me"

Int - "Huh. (beat).  So why do you want to be a window fitter?"

-------

Things got interesting at that point. I don't think the two interview women liked me very much. Things got even more interesting when I tried to explain to them about having a record deal and what that actually means. In fact they seemed mildly interested when I was talking about that. 

The ironic thing is I would actually quite like to work in construction. I enjoy building things. Whereas I hate office jobs. They are far more boring. It is much more challenging to build a straight wall than it is to argue a motion in court or to lead a discussion on  corporate strategy or write an essay about something academic. It is to me anyway.

Also got rejected from a HSBC job today. They advised me to consider re-applying for a "higher profile" role. 

All their "higher profile" roles involve a selection process that takes months I don't have. 

Fuck off HSBC.

It has occured to me that perhaps potential employers think that my CV is a pack of lies. I may have to resort to the highly ironic situation of lying on my CV to make it look less impressive and more average. 

This world makes no sense.

This is my second draft of this post as I phrased the first one so badly.

I want one of my clever computer minded friends to try and explain to me how computers work at the most fundamental level. I have been teaching myself C++ the last few days and it has led me to think about how and why computers work. I get binary code. I understand basic electronics. What I don't get is how the two combine, where the dividing line is between them and what crosses that line.

I think, but am not sure, after dodgy internet research that it is the control unit of the CPU that does this.

so how does the control unit of a CPU work? 

I am amazed that there is so little information available about this on the net. Try doing a search for "how machine code works" and you will see what I mean.

Up- Just spoke to estate agents and things are pretty much set for Bel and I to move to Bidford.

Down - My Dad's hair has started to fall out due to his radiation therapy.

Up- Most things are organised for the wedding.

Down - The strain is getting to my Mum and she is having problems with her mysterious skin infection which for some reason her doctors think can be cured by two seasions of radiation a week. Considering they don't know what is causing the infection I'm not sure it is the best plan I have ever heard. 

I have no faith in Doctors. I used to be in a band with one and it worried me when one drunken night we had an intellectual conversation and she couldn't articulate the difference between and an atom and a molecule. (and she dhadn't even heard of a quark).

Up - Bel is healthy, Lena is healthy and I don't want to break things.

Down - I haven't exercised for a while and can feel bits of me going soft again which shouldn't be soft.

Up - I have discovered that contrary to what I have believed for about ten years, I can in fact draw. Not amazingly or anything, but I can draw things that look like the thing that I am meant to be drawing.

Down - I have been rejected again for being overqualified.

Up - I re-wrote my CV and it sounds impressive. Perhaps too impressive.

Down - I feel slightly guilty about not inviting some people to my wedding.

Up - Team america is out today and Bel and I will go see it.

Down - I am bored of this post now.
Working 12 hour night shifts is bad. mmmmmkay.

I wrote this as a reply to Andy's post but then it ended up being a lot longer than I was expecting.

I too did a Pantera listening tribute last night. 

They were very much of the time weren't they? Out of context they do sound awful. At the time they were great though because no other band were that heavy but also catchy-ish. Apart from Metallica maybe, but they had toned down by 91. Great Southern Trendkill is the only album that doesn't make me cringe now though.

Dimebag was a great guitarist. If you listen carefully, he very rarely plays the same riff twice. That is a lot harder than it sounds. He was my second great guitar influence believe it or not, after I got good enough to realise that playing like Slash was not very technically demanding. He used to write a monthly column in one of the big guitar magazines for a few years. He wrote the only ever decent description I have ever read of how to correctly perform artificial harmonics. It was written with excessive use of swearing and stupid metaphors- like- "pinch that motherfucker til it brays like a greased pig".

He was probably a dick though to be fair. He was from Texas, he liked his guns. He did a lot of drink and drugs and probably was a wife beater or at least not quite a liberally minded politically correct dude. There was also at one time a big thing in the media about how Pantera were very racist and were enciting racism. I know not if there is any truth to that but it wouldn't surprise me.  

He would have probably viewed going out on stage being shot by a fan as quite a good way to go. I just hope that the shooter was nuts or heard the voice of Bette Midler telling him to do it or something. 

I really hope that he wasn't an avid Pantera fan motivated because Damage Manual performed some Pantera songs in their live set. That would be one of the lamest murder motives in history.

Went and picked my parents up from the airport yesterday. Birmingham airport is totally gay. There aren't enough people there to make people watching a fun distraction so I was very very bored and cold waiting for them. 

Then I had a few hours worth of what-we-did-on-holiday-banter which, being as they went back to my Dad's old home town for a large part of their stay, consisted mainly of them meeting people that remembered him from 25 years ago. Everybody knew my Dad because of how his Dad (my namesake) died. I have talked about that on here before so I'm sure most of you know.

Anyway they brought me back a novelty keyring and a hat that says 'Portugal' on it. It differs from the hat that says 'Portugal' on it that they got me last year. This one has a bit of black on it.

The keyring however is fucking ace. It is a really cheap novelty catholic keyring with a depiction of the Virgin Mary appearing to the Lady Fatima in Portugal. It is good cos it is so shit. They bought a bunch of them for my half-sisters and brothers too. For added comedy value they all have our names on. Well mine just has 'Pedro' on it because the rest of my name is too rare but still. funny.

My Dad has started worrying about his soul now that he is dying and he appears to have rediscovered his lost Catholic tendencies from his youth which amuses me no end. He was going to train to be a priest in his early teens. If you have ever met my Dad that mental image should amuse you. Think of a comedy Saddam Hussein in priestly garb with a big comedy grin and glasses and you won't be too far away. 

So yeah he also bought this totally HORRIBLE plastic Virgin Mary statue thing. It has little glass eyes that scare me. Urgh. Forget Chucky.

So after all the holiday coversation was exhausted I went for a run and then started tidying my shit up. I have to live without a bed again and keep all my stuff in boxes for a few weeks. Not fun. Small price to pay for living in my own house and not paying anything for it for 2 years I guess. But still. Gay. 

My jaw aches from talking. In the absence of my parents and Bel I have only spoken to a handful of people in the last two weeks. Mostly on the phone too. Aside from shop assistants I think I only saw Stu and Alex in the flesh. That is not a calculated statement to make you feel sorry for me, I am not a social misfit that can't handle being with people. I have friends, I could go and see them. Come to think of it, most of the time I am the centre of attention in group situations. Mainly because I'm funnier and more openly horrible than most people. Which is always entertaining for others. It actually isn't that much fun for me though (no challenge usually), I'd rather stay home and read a book or write a song. Going out drinking isn't really an option any more. These days I'm too much of a control freak to enjoy getting high or drunk. Besides I always seem to end up fighting someone. Not through choice. Fighting and violence are bad and solve nothing. But piss me off and my desire to smash your head open and feast on the gooey insides outweighs my rationality. There is something about drunk Englishmen that incites me to commit heinous crimes. Dumb cunts.

I appear to be blabbing crap in order to put off my tidying. I better get on with it.

Station bans new 'Bland Aid' song


A radio station has banned the new version of Do They Know It's Christmas after being inundated by listeners claiming it was "rubbish".

Minutes after the updated Band Aid classic was broadcast for the first time the station switchboard was jammed with listeners calling for it to be axed.

Bosses at Pembrokeshire Radio, based in Narbeth, quickly bowed to listener-power and pulled the plug on the new festive single. They pledged to continue backing the single's charitable aim and are advising listeners to buy it anyway - even if it is never played.

"We played it for the first time at 8am today and were amazed at the response from our listeners," said Keri Jones, station DJ and managing director. People were saying it is awful rubbish. They were quite passionate about it - it was quite overwhelming. All the lights on the switchboard lit up and we had about 50 calls within minutes of it being played.

"In the end it got so busy it was pointless answering, everyone was saying the same thing anyway. It's rubbish, more Bland Aid than Band Aid. He added: "We are telling listeners to go out and buy it anyway because it is all in a good cause.

"It may well end up as being this year's Christmas number one, although it's more likely to be used as a coaster rather than be listened to. We banned it because we believe in going with what out listeners say. In the meantime we will continue playing the original."

You know that saying "I hate to say I told you so". Generally it is a big fat lie cos almost everyone enjoys revelling in their superiority, especially me. But not today.

I have been saying for a long time that Bush would win and that he would cheat. I am fairly sure that that is what happened last night. 

I'm not sure how he cheated but I'm sure he did. Logic and common sense tell me so. 

The exit polls had Kerry winning. Not by a whole bunch but significantly enough. Turns out the exit polls were very very wrong. The only time they have been even close to being that wrong was 2000. What happened then? Bush cheated.

One explanation is that a lot of people pretend to be anti-bush but when it comes down to it on their own in the voting booth they choose Bush over Kerry. I buy that for maybe 1%. 

The other explanation is that he cheated. 

Think about it logically. He cheated last time and got away with it. That isn't an incentive to play fair. It is an incentive to do it again but to a greater extent and in a more sophisticated way than last time. the other thing is the voter turnout. It does not make sense that the people who turned out this time were republicans. And if they weren't it makes even less sense that this blow to Bush would be offset by the rest of the voting population. 

Give it 6 months and I bet Michael Moore and other liberal writers will look beneath the surface and they will find some worrying things. 

People don't like to think that someone can cheat on the biggest and most important election on the planet. Let alone twice. That is fair enough I understand that. It is called denial. It is a perfectly human reaction.

Maybe it is because I am English and so distanced from it slightly. Maybe it is because I am fairly well versed in political history and therefore expect candidates to cheat. Maybe it is because I am sceptical and pessimistic. Maybe I just find it hard to believe that there are more dumb cunts in america than people with at least half a brain. 

This election was more important than the last one. The senate and the house are now even more Republican. Bush doesn't have to worry about re-election so he can pursue what passes for his own ideals. 

It is not good.
